      "role": "user",
      "content": "hi, i'm buying my first house and i'm a bit confused. what exactly is escrow? like where does my earnest money actually go after i sign the contract and before we close?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Congratulations on your new home! Escrow is a fund held by a third party, usually an attorney or a title company, that stores money for both the buyer and seller in a real estate transaction. When you sign a contract and make an earnest money deposit, it goes into an escrow account until the transaction is completed. This fund is used to hold down payments, closing costs, and other fees until the sale is finalized. Once closed, the escrow funds are released and divided between the buyer and seller, respectively.",
