      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow companies are typically insured and regulated by government agencies, such as the Federal Insurance Company (FIC) or the Department of Insurance, to ensure they handle funds safely. They're also audited and inspected regularly to maintain their stability. As a buyer, it's your right to request an escrow analysis report, which provides information on the account's balance, transactions, and any outstanding requests. This gives you a clear understanding of your escrow account's activity and ensures your funds are secure.",
