      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow companies go beyond just holding funds; they often manage and facilitate various tasks throughout the transaction process, such as reviewing documents, handling title insurance, and ensuring compliance with legal requirements. They may also pay or reserve funds for the seller's closing costs, hold title or deed transfers, and facilitate wire transfers or check payments. In addition, escrow companies often provide additional services, like handling outstanding tax payments or liens, to ensure a smooth transaction.",
